text.__SUMMARY__: Letheobia sudanensis, also known as the Garamba gracile blind snake or Sudan baked snake, is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family. It is endemic to Africa.
text.Further reading: Schmidt, K.P. et al. 1923. Contributions to the herpetology of the Belgian Congo based on the collection of the American Museum Congo Expedition, 1909-1915: Part II.-Snakes. Bull. Amer. Mus. Nat. Hist. 49(1):1-146. (Typhlops sudanensis, pp. 51–53.)
